We will NOT create new utility files yet.

---

## WHEN WE SPLIT FILES

We split ONLY when:

* File becomes hard to read
* Code is reused
* Unit testing becomes difficult
* Responsibility becomes mixed

Trigger threshold:

~500 lines

---

## OUTPUT FORMAT STANDARD

All executions will produce:

The following test cases were created in <file path>

1. test_name
2. test_name

---

pytest execution results:

<pytest output>

---

TOTAL:

X tests
Y passed
Z failed

---

## ERROR HANDLING RULE

Never swallow exceptions.

Always:

Log
Return structured result

---

## LOGGING RULE

All major steps must log:

Starting generation
Writing file
Running pytest
Execution complete

---

## UNIT TEST REQUIREMENT

Every function added or modified must have:

At least one unit test.

Minimum test types:

Success case
Failure case

---

## REFACTORING RULE

We refactor only when:

* Behavior is stable
* Tests are passing
* Change improves clarity

Never refactor during debugging.

---

## NEXT ARCHITECTURAL GOAL

Stabilize:

Coding Agent Execution Flow

Not:

New features
New agents
New directories

